                            <comment id="14709187" author="oneiros" created="Mon, 24 Aug 2015 12:38:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If we use (instead of &lt;tt&gt;sys:usedLogger&lt;/tt&gt;) &lt;tt&gt;syslog&lt;/tt&gt; or &lt;tt&gt;SYSLOG_FAILOVER&lt;/tt&gt;, logging to files works; it&apos;s only the indirection through &lt;tt&gt;Failover&lt;/tt&gt; (or &lt;tt&gt;sys:usedLogger&lt;/tt&gt;) that does not work.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14709195" author="oneiros" created="Mon, 24 Aug 2015 12:44:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;See also &lt;a href=&quot;http://stackoverflow.com/q/28276619/821436&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://stackoverflow.com/q/28276619/821436&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;http://stackoverflow.com/a/31194308/821436&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://stackoverflow.com/a/31194308/821436&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
